content:
Insurance Policyholder Digital Experience Site

The Policyholder Digital Experience site provides policyholders with access to view and change important information about their account, policies, and billing options.

This site contains a variety of components that allow users to self-manage some parts of their policies. These components are customizable FlexCards that can be compiled into Lightning web components for use on the site.

The Policyholder site template includes two top-level pages: Home and Policies.

On the Home page, policyholders can:

* See plans they are enrolled in
* View a statement for these plans
* Enroll in a plan during open enrollment
* Update account information

Policyholders also have access to a policy record page for each of their policies. On this page, users can see all their policies and click on each one to view its overview.

Customization is required for the Policyholder site components.
title: Policyholder Digital Experience Site
